can we just exec `npm run build:css` to have only one place the define how to build the css and not forget to update one if needed ? 

Otherwise +1; 

one gotcha though it does not fail is `lessc` not installed... strangely.

You can save a few characters:

for (expr* arg : *term) {
     ...
}

I'll expand this a bit locally to explain --

```js
// getInitialProps is a function unique to next.js, not normal to React
static getInitialProps
// Apparently our flow setup doesn't have this definition already situated
// The first (and only?) argument is an object
// which has a property called renderPage
({ renderPage }:
// Everything after the ":" is the actual type definition for this
// so we're saying the type of this argument is an object with property renderPage,
// which is a Function (which I could have typed out the type of more explicitly --
// I aimed for passing for now)
{ renderPage: Function })
```

nice decorator, thanks for the tip. I wonder why do they require `__eq__` to be implemented if `__lt__` is available.

```
def __eq__(self, o):
  return (not (self < o) ) and (not (o < self))
```
